# Z Commit Rules

- Make minimal, reversible, and auditable changes.
- Keep claims in commits and docs aligned with verified repository truth.
- Do not bypass review controls or imply production promotion from documentation-only changes.
- Prefer small scoped commits with clear intent and rollback friendliness.
- Preserve governance-first workflow: read doctrine, verify scope, validate changes, open PR, await human approval.
